# API Service Layer

## Organization (`src/services/`)

| File | Domain |
|---|---|
| `api.ts` | Base RTK Query setup, auth interceptor, retry logic |
| `constants.ts` | All API URL constants, environment-specific base URLs |
| `types.ts` | Shared request/response types |
| `authService.ts` | Login, MFA, SSO, password reset, change password |
| `rosterService.ts` | Roster CRUD, upload, publish, download |
| `employeeDBService/` | Employee database v2 (module pattern) |
| `employeeDBServicev3/` | Employee database v3 (module pattern) |
| `employeeDetailsService/` | Employee profile details (module pattern) |
| `leavesService/` | Leave management (module pattern) |
| `attendanceService/` | Attendance tracking (module pattern) |
| `absenceService/` | Absence records (module pattern) |
| `swapService.ts` | Shift swap operations |
| `configurationService.ts` | Work rules, team capacity, leave quota |
| `manageOrgService.ts` | Organization hierarchy |
| `studioService.ts` | Studio management |
| `studioTrackerService.ts` | Real-time studio tracking |
| `notificationsService.ts` | Push notification subscription |
| `gpSchedules.ts` | GP schedule views |

## Module Pattern (Required for Complex Services)

```
featureService/
  featureService.ts   → RTK Query endpoint definitions
  types.ts            → Request/response interfaces
  index.ts            → Re-exports (barrel file)
```

Use this pattern when a service has 5+ endpoints or complex types. Simple services (< 5 endpoints) can be single files.

## Environment URL Resolution

Base URLs resolve from `env` cookie via `getBaseUrl()` in constants:

```
LOCAL/DEV     → https://ppworkforce361-api.arriselabs.com
QA            → https://ppworkforce360-api-qa.arriselabs.com
UAT           → https://ppworkforce360-api-uat.arriselabs.com
PRODUCTION    → https://ppworkforce360-api.arriselabs.com
```

Each region (RO, BG, RS) has its own URL set. URL constants: `IAM_URL`, `ROSTER_URL`, `EMPLOYEE_DB_URL`, `LEAVES_URL`, `NOTIFICATION_URL`, etc.

## Response Transformation

Raw API responses are transformed in `@/utils/responseModifiers.ts` — not inline in components:

- `modifyFilterResponse()` — filter dropdown data
- `modifyLeaveFilterResponse()` / `modifySwapFilterResponse()` — with localization
- `transformEmployeeDataResponse()` — employee profile sections
- `getEmpDetails()` — region-aware field filtering

## File Uploads

```typescript
uploadFile: build.mutation({
  query: (formData: FormData) => ({
    url: joinPath(BASE_URL, 'upload'),
    method: HTTPMethods.POST,
    body: formData,  // NO JSON.stringify — RTK Query sends FormData natively
  }),
}),
```

## File Downloads

Use `downloadFileHandler()` from `@/utils/download` — handles blob creation, filename extraction from `X-Filename` header, and DOM cleanup.

## Error Handling Chain

1. RTK Query `baseQueryWithReauth` catches 401/403 → token refresh → retry
2. 503 errors trigger exponential backoff (max 3 retries)
3. Component-level: check `isError` / `error` from RTK Query hooks
4. User notification: `showToast({ type: 'error', ... })`
5. **Never silently swallow errors** — every API call must surface failures

## Anti-Patterns

- **No raw `fetch` in components or hooks** — only `api.ts` uses raw fetch for token refresh
- **No manual `useEffect` + `useState` for API calls** — use RTK Query hooks
- **No `console.log` of API responses in services** — remove before committing
- **No request cancellation (AbortController) exists yet** — be aware long-running requests are not cancelled on unmount
